definition.value: An oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 2-oxobutanoic acid in which both of the hydrogens at position 3 are substituted by methyl groups and one of the hydrogens at position 4 is substituted by a hydroxy group.

A cyclohexadienecarboxylic acid that is cyclohexa-2,4-dienecarboxylic acid which is substituted at positions 1 and 6 by hydroxy groups which are both on the same side of the plane of the cyclohexadiene ring.

A benzenoid aromatic compound that consists of two benzene rings connected by a single covalent bond. Biphenyl occurs naturally in coal tar, crude oil, and natural gas. Formerly used as a fungicide for citrus crops.
